Pytorch is already available on the Agave cluster through the anaconda/py2 and anaconda/py3 modules, depending on the version you desire.

In anaconda/py2, there's the pytorch environment:

$ module load anaconda/py2
$ conda env list
# conda environments:
#
...
additional environments omitted for space, such as tensorflow, caffe, etc.
pytorch                  /packages/7x/anaconda2/5.2.0/envs/pytorch
...
$ source activate pytorch

In anaconda/py3, there's additional pytorch environments:

$ module load anaconda/py3
$ conda env list
# conda environments:
#
...
additional environments omitted for space, such as tensorflow, caffe, etc.
pytorch                  /packages/7x/anaconda3/5.3.0/envs/pytorch
pytorch-1.20             /packages/7x/anaconda3/5.3.0/envs/pytorch-1.20
pytorch-gpu              /packages/7x/anaconda3/5.3.0/envs/pytorch-gpu
...

$ source activate pytorch-gpu
(pytorch-gpu) $